The paper deals with matrix recovery, which is a problem in signal processing and machine learning. The use of algebraic geometry tools suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS), which further supports these sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of measurements to recover matrices, which could fall under the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
